    "id": "m7pup4ak",
    "chapterId": "aldehyde-and-ketone",
    "exam": "BITSAT",
    "title": "BITSAT 2024",
    "year": "2024",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "type": "SCQ",
    "question": "Which of the following compounds will undergo self aldol condensation in the presence of cold dilute alkali?",
    "options": [
      "$ \\mathrm{CH}_{2}=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CHO} $",
      "$ \\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CHO} $",
      "$ \\mathrm{C}_{6} \\mathrm{H}_{5} \\mathrm{CHO} $",
      "$ \\mathrm{CH}_{3} \\mathrm{CH}_{2} \\mathrm{CHO} $"
    ],
    "correctOptionIndex": 3,
    "solution": "<p>Aldehydes which contain $ \\alpha $-hydrogen on a saturated carbon, i.e. $ \\mathrm{CH}_{3} \\mathrm{CH}_{2} \\mathrm{CHO} $ will undergo aldol condensation.</p><p>Although $ \\mathrm{CH}_{2}=\\stackrel{\\alpha}{\\mathrm{C}} \\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{CHO} $ also contain a $ \\alpha $-hydrogen atom but cannot be easily abstracted by a base to form a carbanion and hence does not undergo aldol condensation.</p>",
    "marks": 3,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "topic": "General",
    "questionType": "NUMERICAL"
  },
  {
    "id": "mnsiiq5h",
    "chapterId": "aldehyde-and-ketone",
    "exam": "BITSAT",
    "title": "BITSAT 2025",
    "year": "2025",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "type": "SCQ",
    "question": "<p>Identify the compound that undergoes self-aldol condensation in the presence of cold dilute alkali, forming a $\\beta$-hydroxy aldehyde:</p>\n",
    "options": [
      "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CHO}$</p>\n",
      "<p>$\\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CHO}$</p>\n",
      "<p>$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{CHO}$</p>\n",
      "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$</p>"
    ],
    "correctOptionIndex": 3,
    "solution": "<p>Aldol condensation requires the presence of at least one $\\alpha$-hydrogen in the aldehyde. Among the options, acetaldehyde $\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}\\right)$ has $\\alpha$-hydrogens and undergoes the reaction.</p>\n<p>$$ 2 \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}+\\text { dilute } \\mathrm{NaOH}\\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}(\\mathrm{OH}) \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CHO} \\text { (3-hydroxy butanal) } $$</p>\n<p>This $\\beta$-hydroxy aldehyde may further dehydrate to form an $\\alpha, \\beta$-unsaturated aldehyde:</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}(\\mathrm{OH}) \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CHO} \\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CHCHO}+\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O} $$</p>\n<p>The other compounds either lack $\\alpha$-hydrogens or are deactivated (e.g., benzaldehyde, phenylacetylene derivative).</p>",
    "marks": 3,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "topic": "General",
    "questionType": "NUMERICAL"
  },
